page.title: 10A TYPICAL DAY IN 1985
page.content: I wake up at 7.30 on all week-days.I go downstairs and have a cup of tea and get dressed and brush my teeth.Then I come downstairs again and if I'm sandwich dinners I get them ready. I watch TV-AM.At 10 to 9 I set off to school with my sister.I arrive at school at about 9.00.School starts at 10 past 9.Then we have some lessons. We have three breaks every day.Dinner break is our longest break.I walk home by myself.On Tuesday I do horse-riding and on Thursday I do guitar.I go to bed at 8.30. On Saturday I go to football practice. I set off for Kelvedon playing field. I collect my friend James.At the playing field we see our manager Vaughn then we start by running round the pitch and then we do some shooting at goal.Finally we have a match.
